  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "As for a default Error widget:\r\n\r\nI see it as a developer tool rather than a production tool. In a production env Algolia is supposed to always work. The only generic message we could display would be \"The search functionnality is not working, please try to reload your browser\" (or something like that). And this message would probably never be shown (but if someone kills both of our DNS providers).\r\n\r\nAs as developer I would like to see the actual error message inlined, that would help me debugging things easily if my devtools are not opened and the API had an error.\r\n\r\n```js\r\nsearch.addWidget(instantsearch.widgets.onError({\r\n  templates: {\r\n    message: function(error) { return '..' }\r\n  }\r\n});\r\n```",
